Society for Education Studies Seminar Series 
 
This grant builds on the successful event I convened at the British Academy in November 2015 on Education, Security and Intelligence Studies, following publication of the Guest Edited Special Issue of the British Journal of Educational Studies on Education, Security and Intelligence Studies. 

The seminar series, which incorporates a strong multi-disciplinary element from the AHRC political theologies grant, provides an opportunity for a network of interested and interdisciplinary partners to provide a coherent programme of nationwide seminars on the theme of education, security and intelligence studies.

The lead institutions involved, linked to their seminars, are in summary:

Seminar 1
Theme
Education, Security and Intelligence: 
National and international contexts 

Department of Education, University of Oxford
Institutions collaborating: Department of Education, University of Oxford; Oxford Centre for Intelligence Studies, Nuffield College, University of Oxford; University of Buckingham, University of East London; University of Bath. 

